<P>
"Bride of the Re-Animator" -- the sequel to the cult pic, "Re-Animator," about 
the bizarre experiments of med student Herbert West -- begins shooting in and 
around L.A. in June. Producer/director Brian Yuzna is casting, but Jeffrey 
Combs (who played West in the original) is as yet unsigned. 
</P>
<P>
The sequel finds West attempting to "revive" his late girlfriend. Like "I," 
said Yuzna, "it will have a satirical bent." 
</P>
<P>
A casting notice sure does. Consider: "(The bride is) a patchwork quilt of old 
body parts . . . (but) she goes to pieces when he rejects her." And for West: 
"Totally and irrevocably bonkers." 
