<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARSENIO HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arsenio Hall is constantly being told that he is "too black" for mainstream 
America. Does anyone ever consider the vast audience that is going untapped 
because Johnny Carson and Pat Sajak are "too white" (and bland) for the youth 
and minorities of America? I'm sorry that Washington Post TV critic Tom Shales 
feels left out when watching "The Arsenio Hall Show." At least he has the 
option of turning the dial to Carson, Sajak or Letterman. Isn't that why we 
have more than one channel on the tube? Why not give Arsenio Hall a chance to 
be his own man and see what America thinks? 
</P>
<P>
CAROL DANCY BAPTISTE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
