<P>
A hearty rooof, rooof, rooof to Arsenio Hall for his efforts to entertain 
audiences while maintaining his own cultural uniqueness and style. I suggest 
that the so-called mainstream WASP America give African-Americans and other 
people of color the dignity of their own cultural expression. It would go a 
long way in relieving you of the burden of your own cultural elitism and at the 
same time expose you to a diversity of ethnic expression that can only be a 
learning experience for the better. 
</P>
<P>
RONALD BROWN 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne 
