<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK: GREAT WHITE "TWICE SHY." CAPITOL **: ALBUMS ARE RATED ON A SCALE 
OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE STARS (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANISS GARZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This group of old school rock 'n' rollers kicks back on its latest LP and tries 
for more of a pop angle. It keeps a few of the metal trappings -- a guitar 
crunch here, some bump-and-grind drums there -- so it won't lose its hard rock 
audience, but songs like "Move It" and "House of Broken Love" seem obviously 
slated for the Top 40 crowd. When tattooed party dude Jack Russell attempts to 
pass himself off as a sensitive guy by warbling "The Angel Song," it just plain 
doesn't work. Great White needs to get real and get down.JANISS GARZA 
