<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEAK MOMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What would it take to please Martin Bernheimer? I attended the Metropolitan 
Opera's monumental production of Wagner's "Ring" cycle, and I suspect that few 
in the international, musically sophisticated audience would agree with 
Bernheimer's article in the May 7 Calendar. 
</P>
<P>
Bernheimer nit-picks over details of the scenery and props, while failing to 
give us an overall picture of the power of the performance. 
</P>
<P>
The opera lover goes to the theater in hopes of experiencing those peak moments 
in which he is, to borrow C.S. Lewis' phrase, "surprised by joy." 
</P>
<P>
Alas, there is no joy in a Bernheimer review, and this time I fear that the 
mighty critic has indeed struck out. 
</P>
<P>
JULIA HEARD 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
