<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN GREEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Composer John Green, who died May 15, used to tell the story that he met a girl 
he was trying to impress. 
</P>
<P>
"Let's go to George Gershwin's place," he suggested. "You know George 
Gershwin?" she asked. "Sure, I know George." 
</P>
<P>
Gershwin was playing the piano when they walked in. George looked up, saw 
Johnny and said, "Hi ya, Brown." 
</P>
<P>
BILL DANNIES 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes 
</P>
