<HEADLINE>
<P>
X-RATED PLAY? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Movies are rated as "G," "Parental discretion recommended" or "X," but I am 
shocked to find that plays are not rated. 
</P>
<P>
I took my mother out of a nursing home in a wheelchair to see "Minamata" 
because we were told by a very skillful telemarketing person that this was a 
play about Japan. I was further told by the ticket office that most people 
loved it -- that there was lots of singing and dancing. 
</P>
<P>
My mother, who is half-paralyzed from a stroke, almost had another stroke when 
we saw on stage men having sex with women and men having sex with men. Many of 
the scenes had naked performers. 
</P>
<P>
Only with the greatest imagination could you believe this was a story about 
Japan. 
</P>
<P>
I was told this was the best play of the season. I have demanded my season 
subscription of $132 be refunded. I was told: no, I might enjoy the rest of the 
season! 
</P>
<P>
CHERI SAKAI 
</P>
<P>
Culver City 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
