follow a trail to the summit. ; Photo, COLOR, Maligne Lake, the second-largest 
glacier-fed lake in the world, is located in a beautiful setting amid the 
snow-capped peaks of the Canadian Rockies. ELSA DITMARS; Map, JASPER NATIONAL 
PARK / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
