<P>
TRAVEL NEWS AND BRIEFS: CANADA NIGHT AIR FARES, FREE FAR EAST LECTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Nighthawk" fares have been introduced between June 17 and Sept. 8 by Air 
Canada for flights from Los Angeles to Toronto, Montreal or Ottawa. The 
round-trip price of $345 to Toronto and $393 to the other two cities is 
available only for trips from Los Angeles on nightly flight 794 and returning 
on flight 793. Tickets must be bought 30 days in advance. Other restrictions 
apply. For more information, call (800) 422-6232. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Geographical Society is the sponsor of a free slide show and 
lecture, "Compelling Connections; a Discussion of Costa Rica," by Katherine 
Nava. The lecture will be presented at 8 p.m. on Friday in Franklin Hall 101, 
Los Angeles City College, 855 N. Vermont Ave., Los Angeles. For more 
information, call (213) 669-4228. 
</P>
<P>
A free lecture on Malaysia, Singapore and Thailand will be given by 
photographer Mort Loveman at 1 p.m. on Wednesday5 in the Roxbury Memorial Park 
clubhouse, 471 S. Roxbury Drive, Beverly Hills. More information may be 
obtained by calling (213) 550-4761. 
</P>
<P>
The turquoise-and-yellow aircraft of Paradise Island Airlines, owned by 
entertainer Merv Griffin, recently began daily round-trip service between Miami 
and Fort Lauderdale airports and the new Paradise Island airport in the 
Bahamas. For more information, call (800) 327-2521. 
</P>
<P>
Braniff has moved its corporate headquarters to 9955 Benford Road, Orlando, 
Fla. 32827. Telephone (407) 856-8000. 
</P>
<P>
Between now and Sept. 8, Air Canada is offering business travelers a half-price 
option on each of its North American routes, except those to or from Florida. 
Under the program, travelers who buy a regularly priced Executive Class ticket 
can receive a 50% discount on a second ticket for a spouse or other family 
member. 
</P>
<P>
Beginning June 1, Northwest Airlines will offer nonstop service three times a 
week between Los Angeles and Osaka, Japan. Flights will leave Los Angeles on 
Monday, Thursday and Saturday at 12:15 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Lufthansa will begin a new service between Los Angeles and Dusseldorf on June 
13. The non-stop service will operate twice weekly, with the flight continuing 
on to Munich. An introductory round-trip fare of $699 to either city will be 
available between June 13 and July 13. For additional information, call (800) 
645-3880. 
</P>
<P>
European city tours from 8 to 14 days are described in free brochures available 
from Club Universe. Six itineraries are offered. Cities included in various 
combinations are London, Paris, Rome, Amsterdam and Lucerne. For more 
information, call (800) 468-6600. 
