<HEADLINE>
<P>
AND MORE WOES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the Consumer Report on Amtrak's problems, hundreds of cars are in 
storage while Amtrak refuses to use anything but Superliners on the western 
transcontinental routes. Besides a shortage of accommodations, 
three-days-a-week service on some routes and a complete lack of service on 
others, this policy leads to a lack of dining and lounge cars for trains that 
split into sections bound for different destinations. Further, the "California 
Zephyr" runs right through Colorado's Glenwood Canyon, where the scenery 
inspired the invention of the dome car, but the only dome in sight is the model 
on the monument that marks the spot. 
</P>
<P>
THOMAS LEE BOLES 
</P>
<P>
Albuquerque 
</P>
