<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: TITLE FIRMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Burbank-based World Title Co. has made two executive promotions: Thomas Hooker 
has been named senior vice president and manager of its Los Angeles County 
operations and Doug Howry has been named manager of operations for Orange, San 
Diego, Riverside and San Bernardino counties. They will be working out of the 
Burbank and Bakersfield offices, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Insurers 
</P>
<P>
Daniel E. Powell, president of CitiPacific Real Estate Services in West Los 
Angeles, has been appointed to the California State Senate's Advisory 
Commission of Real Property Insurance. The commission is to aid the Senate 
committee on insurance, claims and corporations, and to help draft legislation 
when appropriate. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Real Estate Lawyers 
</P>
<P>
Robert A. Kendall has joined the firm of Floyd Sayer Associates, located in Los 
Angeles. The firm specializes in real estate and construction law. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
