Consultants 
</P>
<P>
The mechanical systems consulting firm of Ludovise &amp; Associates has 
promoted Robert Scott to vice president. The Newport Beach-based company's 
experience is in commercial, industrial and institutional developments. Scott 
will supervise all its projects and internal systems administration, plus its 
new business development. 
</P>
<P>
Kotin, Regan &amp; Mouchly Inc., a national real estate consulting firm located 
in Brentwood, has appointed Thomas R. Jirovsky vice president and chief 
financial officer. Jirovsky specializes in financial planning and design and 
development of computerized financial models for the company's public and 
private clients. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Accountants 
</P>
<P>
David W. Robinson has joined the Westside accounting firm of Lam &amp; Isaac as 
a principal. The firm provides a full range of tax and accounting services to 
the real estate industry. Robinson, with 12 years of public accounting 
experience, will be active in all areas. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Architects 
</P>
<P>
Kenneth R. Long has been appointed senior associate of Altoon &amp; Porter 
Architects. Long will be responsible for all phases of a project from 
conceptual planning and design through construction documents. He will also be 
involved with client relations and business development aspects of the Los 
Angeles firm. 
</P>
<P>
Douglas H. Austin, president of San Diego-based Austin Hansen Fehlman Group, 
has been selected to chair the Dean's Advisory Council for the School of 
Architecture and Environmental Design at San Luis Obispo's California 
Polytechnic University. The council advises the faculty on course curriculum, 
scholarship programs and resource opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
Widom Wein Cohen has made two appointments: Jorge Sciupac as director of 
architecture, managing the company's mixed-use development projects, as well as 
monitoring its technical product; and, Lisa Pound as executive director, 
overseeing office staffing and business/financial planning. The company, 
located in Santa Monica, offers architecture, interior design and planning 
services to developer, health care and corporate clients. 
</P>
<P>
Wallace D. Palmer has joined Kober Rippon Associates of Los Angeles as director 
of business development. The more than 50-year-old firm specializes in 
hotels/resorts, retail, offices, educational facilities and industrial building 
projects in the United States and abroad. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson/Takahashi/Katz &amp; Associates has promoted Ben Davis, Dwight 
Clements, Mandana Motahari and William So to project managers. The 
architectural firm, located in Los Angeles, focuses on health care, commercial 
and industrial design. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Civil Engineers 
</P>
<P>
Susan L. Bok has joined the governmental relations group of Psomas &amp; 
Associates as a senior planner. The firm, founded in 1946 by George Psomas, is 
an independent civil engineering company with headquarters in Santa Monica and 
offices in Costa Mesa, Riverside and Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Developers/Builders 
</P>
<P>
Thomas E. Heggi has been named president of Watt Southern California, a new 
Tustin-based residential subsidiary of Watt Enterprises established to build 
single-family detached housing for move-up markets in Orange, Riverside and San 
Bernadino counties. 
</P>
<P>
EastLake Development Co. has promoted Katy Wright to project manager. She will 
assist in processing entitlements and implementing plans for EastLake III, a 
master-planned community in Chula Vista. The firm is based in San Diego. LINDA 
MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
