<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
VICTIMS SOUGHT IN OHIO BRIDGE COLLAPSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Helicopters hovered over a tributary of the Ohio River searching for an 
undetermined number of people whose vehicles plunged into the rain-swollen 
waterway when a temporary bridge collapsed shortly before it was to be closed 
to traffic. Powerful currents prevented authorities from finding any victims or 
their vehicles. The American Red Cross said at least seven people remained 
unaccounted for. Officials are uncertain how many vehicles fell when a 100-foot 
section of the bridge near Cincinnati gave way. Eyewitness accounts differed 
but authorities believed at least two vehicles disappeared into the Great Miami 
River's rushing, muddy water. County engineers said the bridge had been ordered 
closed because of debris that was pinned against it, but the collapse occurred 
before workers could arrive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
