</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Jewish community in the West German city of Frankfurt said it is taking 
court action against a city council member from an ultra-rightist party over 
alleged anti-Semitic remarks. Erich Gutjahr, a 78-year-old member of the 
rightist National Party of Germany, was quoted by the Frankfurt Allgemeine 
newspaper as saying: "Jews have bought up half the city. The Jews are 
plundering us again. Something must be done about this." The city prosecutor's 
office said it is investigating Gutjahr for possible violation of German laws 
over the statements, and several members of the city council have demanded that 
he resign. Gutjahr said he is not anti-Semitic and only wants to protect 
"German interests," the paper reported. 
</P>
