<HEADLINE>
<P>
SINGAPORE HANGS 2 AS DRUG TRAFFICKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SINGAPORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Singaporean drug traffickers were hanged Friday for trafficking in nearly 
45 pounds of drugs in 1982, a prison spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Singapore has hanged 24 drug traffickers since 1975 when it introduced a 
mandatory death penalty for anyone convicted of trafficking in more than half 
an ounce of heroin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
