<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
FORUM ON GOLF COURSE, RESORT PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Development of two luxury resorts on the Palos Verdes Peninsula coast and four 
golf courses will be the topic of forum at the Rancho Palos Verdes City Council 
meeting at 8 p.m. Tuesday at Hesse Park, 29301 Hawthorne Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
"We will try to look at the coastline as a whole and get a comprehensive 
picture of what is happening on the coast," said Robert Benard, city 
environmental services director. The staff will present information on the 
projects and hear public comment and questions. 
</P>
<P>
On the agenda are specific proposals filed with the city for a 575-room hotel, 
conference center and golf course on the former Marineland site, and a 450-room 
Ritz-Carlton resort hotel, golf course and residential development near the 
Rancho Palos Verdes-San Pedro boundary. 
</P>
<P>
There will also be discussion of a possible public golf course built on 
undeveloped portions of Point Vicente Park. The park encompasses the Civic 
Center and the Point Vicente Interpretive Center. Also on the agenda is a 
discussion of plans by a Chicago and Los Angeles group to build a residential 
and golf development on land it owns north of the park. 
</P>
<P>
Before the forum, the council, Planning Commission, and traffic, transit, 
recreation and parks and trails committees will discuss coastal developments. 
That session begins at 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The 8 p.m. meeting will be aired live on public access cable Channel 3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
