10 HURT DURING BRAWL AT PRISON IN NEW YORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COXSACKIE, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least seven prisoners and three corrections officers were injured when a 
brawl broke out as hundreds of black and Latino inmates milled about in a 
prison yard, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
A small group of inmates started a fight that quickly escalated Friday at 
Greene Correctional Facility, a corrections spokesman said. About 80 inmates 
were transferred to other facilities Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Prison officials were investigating what caused the violence. 
</P>
