<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFTER THE DEATH OF DEBBIE KILLELEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the sentencing of Danny Ornelas for the death of my beautiful wife, Debbie 
Killelea, it is time for my friends and my family to end a very tragic chapter 
in our lives. 
</P>
<P>
Each day is a struggle for my children and myself without Deb, but as time 
passes and with the spiritual and emotional help of our friends and faith, we 
will manage to survive this very painful period. It is difficult for me to 
believe that the pain caused by the loss of Deb will ever die, but I pray that 
one day the sorrow will be replaced by our fond memories of a loving and giving 
wife and mother. 
</P>
<P>
My faith allows me to believe that Deb had served her time on earth and is now 
in a better place. One day, Michael, Hillary, Joseph and myself will be 
reunited with her to again enjoy her warm smile, her positive view of life and 
her special sense of humor. These convictions truly give me and my family the 
strength to continue. 
</P>
<P>
With the end of a chapter we can look forward to the next, and I wish to begin 
by thanking my church, family, and friends and all those unknown people who 
have prayed and helped my children and myself. At this time I encourage 
everyone affected by this tragedy to continue with their lives, as we must. Deb 
would want us all to move on and to forgive. 
</P>
<P>
BRIAN M. KILLELEA 
</P>
<P>
Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
