<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE HOMELESS SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the May meeting of the Orange County Homeless Initiatives Task Force, two 
representatives of the homeless in Santa Ana told the members that, during a 
recent sweep, Santa Ana police officers seized the medicine of a homeless 
woman, suffering from epilepsy. One hour later the victim of this confiscation 
suffered an epileptic seizure. 
</P>
<P>
This allegation was heard by about 40 members of the task force, who represent 
city and volunteer organizations throughout Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
I think you will agree with us that this matter should be investigated by Santa 
Ana immediately, and the results of the investigation should be published. 
</P>
<P>
Besides blackening the name of Santa Ana before the whole of Orange County, the 
cruelty and possible illegality of such sweeps should be apparent to even the 
most hardhearted citizen of your city. We have been assured that these sweeps 
are in violation of a court order in an existing lawsuit. 
</P>
<P>
Surely Santa Ana does not consider this to be a reasonable answer to the 
national crisis of homelessness. 
</P>
<P>
SYLVIA EASTON 
</P>
<P>
Chairwoman of Irvine Task Force 
</P>
<P>
for the Homeless 
</P>
</TEXT>
