<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL, SOFTBALL AND TENNIS PLAYOFF SITES ANNOUNCED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pairing sites for Tuesday's Southern Section playoffs in baseball and softball 
and Wednesday's team tennis championship were announced Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-A baseball semifinal between Kennedy High School (23-5) and Tustin (21-8) 
is tentatively set for 3:15 p.m. at UC Irvine's Anteater Field. A 5-A semifinal 
matching El Dorado (21-8) and Lakewood (25-3) will be held at 4 p.m. at Blair 
Field in Long Beach. That game will be the first of a doubleheader, with the 
other semifinal between Hacienda Heights Wilson and Long Beach Millikan 
scheduled at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
In 4-A softball, Western (24-5) will play Kennedy (20-4) at Cypress Park. In 
3-A, Mission Viejo (17-8) will play Ramona (22-7) at Alicia Park in Mission 
Viejo. Both games are set for 3:15 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-A tennis final Wednesday between Woodbridge (18-4) and Sunny Hills (21-1) 
will be held at the Sunny Hills Racquet Club at 3:15 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
